---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Security — Ringdocket"
  description="How Ringdocket handles your data. Row-level security, JWT-verified routes, Keychain-stored tokens, no recording, no third-party tracking."
>
  <main class="prose-page">
    <p class="kicker mono">Security</p>
    <h1>The smallest data footprint we can ship.</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      Call-blocker apps have a bad track record. Most of them ask for your
      contacts, fingerprint your device for ad networks, and quietly broker
      your phone activity to data brokers. Ringdocket does none of that.
      Here's the actual posture, with the controls named so you can verify
      it.
    </p>

    <h2>Data handling</h2>
    <ul class="rules">
      <li>
        <strong>Row-level security on every Supabase table.</strong> Default
        deny, granted selectively. Any new migration that adds a table ships
        with <code class="mono">ALTER TABLE ... ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY</code>
        in the same file or it doesn't merge.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Service-role keys are server-side only.</strong> They never
        ship in the iOS bundle, never run in the browser, and never appear in
        a client-readable env var. Privileged writes happen inside Cloudflare
        Workers behind JWT verification.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>User report notes are filtered for PII before write.</strong>
        Worker-layer regex strips E.164 phone patterns and runs a profanity
        filter before anything hits Postgres. Notes never render on public
        pages or analytics surfaces.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>The full IP is dropped after 30 days.</strong> Only the /24
        subnet is retained, used for corroboration de-duplication.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Authentication</h2>
    <ul class="rules">
      <li>
        <strong>Supabase magic-link sign-in.</strong> No passwords stored,
        anywhere. The login link is single-use and expires.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>JWT verification on every authenticated worker route.</strong>
        The token is checked against the Supabase JWKS on each request &mdash;
        no shared session caches across users.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Sessions are short-lived and refresh on activity.</strong>
        A stolen token's window of usefulness is hours, not days.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>iOS app</h2>
    <ul class="rules">
      <li>
        <strong>Tokens live in the Keychain.</strong> Authenticated state is
        confined to the main app target &mdash; <em>not</em> the App Group.
        The Call Directory Extension cannot read your auth token.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Device fingerprint is a UUID v4 in the Keychain.</strong>
        Generated locally at first launch. Reinstalling the app generates a
        new UUID. We do not use Apple's IDFA, and we do not show the App
        Tracking Transparency prompt because we don't need it.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>No call recording.</strong> Audio never leaves your device.
        There is no microphone access requested by the app.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>No contacts access.</strong> The block list is delivered to
        iOS through the Call Directory Extension; matching happens on-device.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>No third-party tracking SDKs.</strong> No Facebook SDK, no
        AppsFlyer, no Branch, no advertising attribution networks. Crash and
        product analytics use pseudonymous IDs only, with phone numbers and
        UUIDs scrubbed before transmission.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Infrastructure</h2>
    <ul class="rules">
      <li>
        <strong>TLS for all traffic.</strong> Device to API, API to Supabase,
        Supabase to subprocessors.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Cloudflare rate limiting</strong> on abuse-prone endpoints
        (signup, report submission, delist form).
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Point-in-Time Recovery</strong> on the primary database.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Audit logs in R2</strong> for forensic review of administrative
        actions.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>What we don't do</h2>
    <p>
      No call recording. No on-device or cloud-side machine learning over
      your personal data. No third-party tracking SDKs. No contacts upload.
      No GPS or precise location. No selling, sharing, or transferring
      personal information to data brokers, advertisers, or any third party
      for commercial purposes. The full statement is in the
      <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>Vulnerability disclosure</h2>
    <p>
      If you've found a vulnerability in Ringdocket, email
      <a href="mailto:security@ringdocket.com">security@ringdocket.com</a>
      with a clear description and steps to reproduce. We respond within
      72 hours. Please do not run automated scans against the production
      domain &mdash; it triggers our rate limiters and creates noise that
      buries real reports.
    </p>
  </main>
</Base>

<style>
  .prose-page {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 4rem) clamp(1rem, 3vw, 2rem) 5rem;
  }
  .kicker {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--accent-signal);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    margin: 0 0 0.875rem;
  }
  h1 {
    font-family: 'Bricolage Grotesque';
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 4.5vw, 2.875rem);
    line-height: 1.05;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    color: var(--ink-primary);
    margin: 0 0 1.25rem;
  }
  h2 {
    font-family: 'Bricolage Grotesque';
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 1.375rem;
    margin: 2.5rem 0 1rem;
    color: var(--ink-primary);
  }
  .lead {
    font-family: 'Newsreader';
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--ink-secondary);
    max-width: 60ch;
    margin: 0 0 2rem;
  }
  p {
    font-family: 'Newsreader';
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--ink-secondary);
    max-width: 64ch;
  }
  .rules {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem;
    font-family: 'Newsreader';
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--ink-secondary);
    max-width: 64ch;
  }
  .rules li {
    padding: 0.6875rem 0 0.6875rem 1.25rem;
    border-bottom: 1px dotted var(--rule-subtle);
    position: relative;
  }
  .rules li:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
  }
  .rules li::before {
    content: '—';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--ink-byline);
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono';
  }
  .rules strong {
    color: var(--ink-primary);
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  a {
    color: var(--ink-primary);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
    text-decoration: none;
  }
  a:hover {
    border-bottom-color: var(--ink-primary);
  }
  code,
  .mono {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono';
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    background: var(--surface-inset);
    padding: 0.125rem 0.375rem;
    border-radius: 3px;
    color: var(--ink-mono);
  }
</style>
